title: Stock Market Outlook Strong As Bullish Patterns Emerge

title: Thousands of companies are asking for tariff exclusions even as US and China push to sign trade deal
text: The overwhelming majority these requests, about 28,000, are under review as of Nov. 1. About 4,900 requests have been granted, while about 10,970 have been denied.

title: The Fed Is Looking Smart
text: Written by: Edward Moya| Oanda The US labor market is still very strong.  The nonfarm payroll report came in much better than expected and the prior month was revised strongly higher.

title: Frenetic Week Ends With Record Highs
text: The busiest remaining week of 2019 appropriately ended with some fireworks with the S&P 500 and Nasdaq setting new all-time record highs, each gaining more than 1.5%.
